Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the @filo pastry sheets{1/2} from the fridge to
allow it to come up to room temperature. Remove from the packet and lay flat on the
counter covered with a damp #tea towel{}. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part
from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Chop the @potatoes{450} into
2cm chunks (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic
press{}). Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the
@British smoked bacon lardons{90} and cook until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the leek
to the bacon and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{4-6%minutes},
stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the potatoes, @boiling water{300%ml}
and @vegetable stock paste{10}.

Stir everything together and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium, then cover
with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer until the potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Stir every few mins to ensure the mixture isn't sticking to the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it becomes too thick or the potatoes haven't yet softened.

While everything simmers, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60}. Once the potatoes are
cooked, stir the @chopped kale{100} into the pan a handful at a time. Cover again and
simmer until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150} and Cheddar.
Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and add salt and pepper if needed,
then transfer into an ovenproof #baking dish{}.

Halve the filo pastry sheets to make squares. Scrunch each sheet into a very loose ball
and place on top of the filling. Repeat until the whole dish is covered, making sure
not to overcrowd the pastry. Drizzle the pie with @olive oil{} and then bake on the
top shelf of your oven until the filo is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @wholegrain mustard{17%g}, @sugar{1} and @olive oil for the dressing{1}
into a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper and mix to combine. Trim the
@baby gem lettuce{1} and separate the leaves. Once the pie is cooked, add the baby
gem to the dressing and toss to coat. Serve the pie on plates with the salad alongside.
Enjoy!

> MOD: If you've chosen to add bacon lardons to your meal, add them to the pan before
> you add the leek. Cook until golden, 3-4 mins. Then add the leek and continue as
> instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook
> lardons thoroughly.